/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
// How to write the server.
/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1) Create the ATL server as usual with the ATL COM AppWizard.

2) When creating the COM class using the ATL Object Wizard, be sure that
   a dual interface is specified.

3) Add only late binding compatible arguments to your method and property
   calls--look in the book or wait for the MIDL compiler warnings.

4) Generate the server and its type library file.



